entity. It features a summary section that reads, \u0022This Wizard will create a Screen from an Entity with these parameters:\u0022 followed by two labeled lines: \u0022Datasource: Priority\u0022 and \u0022List of fields:\u0022 with the fields \u0022Color,\u0022 \u0022Name,\u0022 and \u0022Order\u0022 listed vertically beneath. The interface includes two buttons at the bottom labeled \u0022Start\u0022 and \u0022Cancel.\u0022 The overall purpose of the interface is to guide users through the process of setting up a screen configuration based on specified parameters.\n\n\n  \n After clicking  Start , your new structures will be created: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/235445ef0be1939829f2e9a9e9b17ee70eb24a31.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for a \u0022Create Screen Wizard\u0022 focused on tracking progress. The UI features a section labeled \u0022Progress\u0022 with two columns: \u0022Found In\u0022 and \u0022Type.\u0022 Under \u0022Found In,\u0022 there are three entries, including one marked with a circle and two marked with a check symbol, all indicating different priority levels. The \u0022Type\u0022 column lists three corresponding types: \u0022Data Structure,\u0022 \u0022Screen Section,\u0022 and \u0022Screen.\u0022 At the bottom, there are two buttons: \u0022Show Result\u0022 and \u0022Close.\u0022 The interface is likely designed for users to monitor the progress of screen creation in a software development environment.\n\n\n  \n Click  Show Result  to navigate to the Model Browser under the  Find results  tab: \n   \n You can then click on any of the created items, which will take you to the Model Browser tree where the item is selected (for example, the newly created screen): \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/6fc2417478a6de9406b2ca9fed14fa384d7b770c.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a Model Browser interface, likely for a software application named \u0022myapplication.\u0022 It includes a hierarchical structure with expandable sections such as \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 and \u0022User Interface.\u0022 Within \u0022User Interface,\u0022 there are listed items including \u0022Charts,\u0022 \u0022Dashboard Widgets,\u0022 \u0022Deep Link Categories,\u0022 \u0022Images,\u0022 \u0022Keyboard Shortcuts,\u0022 \u0022Menu,\u0022 \u0022Notification Boxes,\u0022 \u0022Reports,\u0022 \u0022Screen Sections,\u0022 and \u0022Screens.\u0022 The \u0022Data\u0022 section leads to subcategories, and the \u0022Priority\u0022 folder is highlighted under \u0022myapplication,\u0022 which further contains \u0022Organization Management,\u0022 \u0022Root Menu,\u0022 and \u0022Security\u0022 directories. The visual appears to serve as a navigation tool for managing application components and configurations.\n\n\n  \n Double-click on your new screen to view its details: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/898674bcce6917c0bcf406b1ac8a399eba0753fd.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for a screen titled \u0022Priority.\u0022 Located on the left side, the \u0022Data Source\u0022 is labeled as \u0022Priority,\u0022 and it contains fields including \u0022Name,\u0022 which is also set to \u0022Priority,\u0022 and an \u0022Id\u0022 with the value \u0022a481daa1-dfbf-496b-bd36-a78b8eccdc7.\u0022 The package is identified as \u0022myapplication.\u0022 A toolbox section lists various components like \u0022BusinessPartner_CreateMe,\u0022 \u0022BusinessPartner_NewUser,\u0022 and \u0022BusinessUnit,\u0022 among others. The main area features a header titled \u0022Priority\u0022 with navigation controls including buttons for play, pause, previous, and next, as well as indicators for records displayed (0/0). There are three blank input fields visible for user data entry purposes.\n\n\n  \n In this example, the screen contains just one screen section\u2014the one created by the wizard: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1b43c53bbb57a4f8ee608402e41613fe4d3e4ea9.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for managing priority settings within a software application. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:48:38"},"vector":[-0.036846116,-0.00809094,-0.06743801,0.011082305,0.009346468,-0.01405499,-0.0067272033,0.0003815482,0.014337075,0.008463736,0.009822921,-0.026697291,0.01407795,0.02309337,-0.0029070198,0.028380016,0.003488234,0.015277569,0.052763388,0.017225984,-0.016195906,-0.026018368,0.06229214,0.015717095,-0.0015399725,0.0601851,0.01762635,-0.027542947,0.008742128,-0.0041048974,0.0063767643,-0.05753236,0.0013353683,-0.004673886,0.0041748574,-0.021468733,-0.005475733,-0.009732747,-0.036237232,-0.009960707,-0.023146039,0.014642099,-0.0008348195,0.011587736,-0.0030065803,-0.037827794,0.0014540348,-0.0019188238,0.010375149,-0.012065715,-0.043271635,0.012771819,0.023833407,-0.035893124,0.06050538,0.03541518,-0.036849014,-0.018505912,-0.06821142,0.027920324,-0.0014434588,-0.010186606,0.017761324,-0.032440804,0.005115898,0.019675715,-0.05283177,-0.00160757,-0.026469639,-0.05442645,-0.0025970154,0.0317168,-0.021678206,-0.030890739,-0.053566683,0.0065775155,-0.02096766,-0.009192545,-0.031030664,0.046853922,-0.029842637,-0.0032658915,0.0016274118,0.015112807,0.022974532,0.0016440692,-0.032193683,0.09190704,0.029510107,0.02850678,-0.02868061,-0.006989988,0.08523925,-0.05468612,-0.008385222,0.00034667415,-0.04554825,-0.02523962,-0.003458042,0.0039559873,-0.03358344,-0.012198615,-0.054211173,0.008404838,-0.0167407,-0.015285102,0.011918937,-0.007588143,-0.04573101,-0.03758422,0.009586226,0.0036776392,0.025257327,-0.020827156,0.0015179559,-0.004320711,0.0027222654,-0.032910045,0.016567158,0.0075675733,-0.013663783,0.028764969,0.10304137,0.0005187544,-0.0041722246,-0.0011811384,-0.022306327,0.013180354,0.018317388,0.027111866,0.